    {
      "id": "c03b4b5b_2e3439f0",
      "file_path": "clamp-policy/clamppolicy-node-type.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 37,
      "message": "I am not sure what the desired behavior is.  I have not been involved in the detailed discussions about this.  I thought originally CLAMP wanted to added a property to the policy node.  Alex Shatov suggested doing this by creating a new type, derived from dcae.policy.nodes, that simply added the field.   This can be done with a type file (or even with a type definition inside the blueprints).\n\nI pointed out that if we were not able to get a satisfactory resolution of DCAEGEN2-989 (related to type files being available in an environment without Internet connectivity), it would be necessary to package a new type file in some kind of a dummy plugin.  We did resolve DCAEGEN2-989, so all we need to solve the original problem as I understand it is a simple type file.   But I was not involved in the detailed discussions, so I may not understand the problem correctly.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
